This paper is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category as it deals with the characterization of international routing detours in the Internet. It may also belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) category as it mentions privacy-conscious states trying to minimize communication traversing different jurisdictions. Information Theory (cs.IT) is another possible category as the paper deals with analyzing and geolocating BGP prefixes. Signal Processing (cs.SI) and Cybersecurity (cs.CY) are also possible categories as the paper deals with detecting and analyzing suspicious network behavior.
